  "texts": [
    "In the case of a small scale value, the figure shows a more pronounced difference in the change of the PDFs for the two values of µ, indicating that the change in the integrated PDFs due to the q 0 ∼ 1 GeV cut varies rapidly with the µ scale, which is relevant for DY pair masses of several Data q 0 ≃ 0 GeV, qs = 1.0 GeV q 0 = 1 GeV, qs = 1.4 GeV q 0 = 2 GeV, qs = 2.1 GeV GeVs.",
    "There is a different trend at low µ, which corresponds to measurements of pair p T at low invariant masses not yet available at the LHC.",
    "From this, we can conclude that the relative amount of soft gluons removed by the cut changes significantly at low scales, and measurable changes in the value of q s could be expected at low DY pair invariant masses.To investigate the region of very small DY pair invariant masses, we have determined the mass dependence of q s using available measurement obtained at √ s = 27.4 GeV [21], and at √ s = 38.8 GeV [22].",
    "This is shown in Figure 6.This figure shows a weak dependence of q s and the soft gluon contribution on the pair invariant mass.",
    "To achieve masses on the order of several GeV at these collision energies, a large value of the longitudinal momentum fraction carried by a colliding parton, x, is required since Therefore, at this collision energies, DY pairs with low invariant masses are primarily produced at high x from valence contributions, making it unlikely to expect a measurable dependence of q s on DY pair invariant mass."
  ]
